cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.CR, cs.SY, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on analyzing the link layer throughput of multichannel Opportunistic Spectrum Access (OSA) ad hoc networks, which is a networking topic. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the performance of joint spectrum sensing and MAC algorithms, which involves information theory concepts. 
3. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper may touch upon security issues related to spectrum sensing and MAC protocols in OSA networks. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes new protocols and evaluates different design options for collaborative spectrum sensing and MAC protocols, which involves system and control aspects. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper may touch upon the impact of spectrum sensing and MAC protocols on multimedia applications in OSA networks.
